ke and briquettes burn but do not flame if using gas or electric barbecue preheat barbecue with all burners on high turn off center burner and lower outside burners to medium low heat place generous cup hickory chips in each of broiler pans set pans over lit burners place empty broiler pan over unlit burner position grill at least inches above burners remove turkey from brine discard brine pat turkey dry with paper towels place orange wedges in main cavity mix olive oil and sesame oil in small bowl brush over turkey arrange breast side up on grill centering above empty broiler pan cover cook until thermometer inserted into thickest part of thigh registers f adding cup hickory chips and briquettes if using charcoal barbecue to barbecue every minutes about hours for glaze bring all ingredients to simmer in heavy medium saucepan brush glaze over turkey cover and cook until thermometer inserted into thickest part of thigh registers f covering any dark areas of turkey with foil about hour longer transfer turkey to platter tent with foil and let stand minutes Food preservation D__ner kebab Breakfast Charcoal Thermal power station Gumbo Vinegar German cuisine Chicken soup Wok Curry Japanese tea ceremony Chicken Cooking weights and measures Ramen Dairy Hamburger Rice pudding Mayonnaise Risotto Welding Black pepper Carbon dioxide Poker jargon Soul food Beer Russian cuisine Casting Portable stove Soup Internal ballistics Recipe Kitchen Culinary mustard Cuisine of Laos French cuisine Sewage treatment Cincinnati chili Pizza Food Common bean Cuisine of Singapore Maple syrup Chocolate Wine Cuisine of Malaysia McDonald's Cuisine of Africa Menstrual cup Turkish coffee Beef noodle soup Dim sum Dosa Fish and chips Sugar Beverage can stove Grilling Gas metal arc welding Dumpling Yerba mate 